sentences: Sara Bosmans-Benedicts (23 October 1861 – 12 November 1949) was a Dutch pianist and piano pedagogue.
In 1886, Benedicts married fellow Dutch musician Henri Bosmans (1856-1896), principal cellist of the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra.

Widowed in her thirties, with a young child to raise, Sarah Benedicts taught at the Conservatoire of Amsterdam.
Benedicts, in her eighties, was arrested and deported by the Nazi occupation in 1944, but her daughter and others intervened to prevent her further detention.
Sara Bosmans-Benedicts died in 1949, and her grave is in Zorgvlied Cemetery in Amsterdam.
